cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD

This paper deals with analyzing the linguistic structure of question texts in Quora to predict answerability. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with predicting whether a question will be answered or not. Additionally, the paper involves social networks (cs.SI) as it deals with analyzing the community Q&A site Quora. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SD) are less likely sub-categories but cannot be completely ruled out as the paper involves analyzing user behavior on a website.
